==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tetrahedron
<hw>Tet`ra*he"dron</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Tetra-</ets> + Gr. <?/ seat, base, fr. <?/ to sit.]</ety>
<fld>(Geom.)</fld> <def>A solid figure inclosed or bounded by four
triangles.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ In crystallography, the regular tetrahedron is regarded
as the hemihedral form of the regular octahedron.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Regular tetrahedron</b></col> <fld>(Geom.)</fld>, <cd>a
solid bounded by four equal equilateral triangles; one of the five
regular solids.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tetrahexahedral</ent>⟦br⟧
